{"$ambrosia":"aero:interactive:9417ac60-5f60-11ea-8e69-affb2224d7e8:*","$id":"0f6cb920-44e0-11ed-84ed-004c087336be","$workspaceId":"7fff47c0-44d6-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c","$projectId":"86cb0040-44df-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca","annotations":[],"configSchemaVersion":"/pluginGenericSchema/v1","config":{"stage":{"sections":[{"rows":[{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-two","ref":"36057c86-324f-4bc4-b7fd-de68bbad47fc","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Options on other Financial Securities","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"bcb09e26-4c15-4446-94a7-50e4d01daa16"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"f9ecfd4b-5e35-4270-946e-342fc7f14c8f","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Although the most commonly traded options are written on stocks, options on other financial assets do exist. Perhaps the most well known are options on stock indexes such as the S&P 100 index, the S&P 500 index, the Dow Jones Industrial Average index, and the NYSE index. These popular options allow investors to protect the value of their investments from adverse market changes. As we will see shortly, a stock index put option can be used to offset the losses on an investorâ€™s portfolio in a market downturn. Using an option to reduce risk by holding contracts or securities whose payoffs are negatively correlated with some risk exposure is called ","marks":[]},{"data":{"ref":"509e9e95-dabf-4ec5-a90f-6e1d292fbfb9","stage":{"ref":"9edcfb82-4dd2-4688-8bf0-5c5744d12af6","sections":[{"ref":"81abb631-173d-48b7-b33c-dd6426bbe5b6","rows":[{"ref":"28c48ae7-774c-446e-a647-5079161c7ccf","columns":[{"ref":"5b258e6a-5c53-4635-81b6-6a5f8505ea3e","stageElements":[{"ref":"79cf1cd4-e134-4ab7-9c5a-0fa2b2cb9e9d","type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"button","ref":"74c31108-3c0f-4f85-99df-d931771fe284","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"bf842aca-8d12-4eee-aad5-9949b9b35f85","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"To reduce risk by holding contracts or securities whose payoffs are negatively correlated with some risk exposure.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"data":{}}]}}}]}]}]}]}},"nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"hedging","marks":[{"type":"bold"}]}],"object":"inline","type":"key-term","ref":"6e596d16-891d-4781-8915-d2992acc1792"},{"object":"text","text":". Options also allow investors to ","marks":[]},{"data":{"ref":"b2029153-b211-4d83-9953-25639a4cff38","stage":{"ref":"4e8c4667-5087-4b86-b1cf-cdc433152cf0","sections":[{"ref":"5d7cbf81-8b07-43a0-91c3-f8dc3b4b5290","rows":[{"ref":"515c163e-afcf-4f8e-b34e-4fb1f1c4c4d7","columns":[{"ref":"ca814602-7d57-433a-887a-22674b397c4b","stageElements":[{"ref":"0c77bb76-da35-433c-af69-e87798b6702e","type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"button","ref":"387f95b9-914a-4648-b7b7-64feadb02b3b","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"2cbdac76-4296-47da-911b-178dbdef0ceb","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"When investors use securities to place a bet on the direction in which they believe the market is likely to move.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"data":{}}]}}}]}]}]}]}},"nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"speculate","marks":[{"type":"bold"}]}],"object":"inline","type":"key-term","ref":"4ff29c9f-2907-45ab-a67a-051ff3f2470f"},{"object":"text","text":", or place a bet on the direction in which they believe the market is likely to move. By purchasing a call, for example, investors can bet on a market rise with a much smaller investment than they could by investing in the market index itself.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"2af055d8-d397-45ab-9740-6773c78517e7"}]}]}]},{"cssClass":"aside-group Sidebar_1Aside","rows":[{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-two","ref":"04e00cdd-76ed-4fb8-8606-0192a3dd0b3b","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Options Are for More Than Just Stocks","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"fd3810ac-0eb5-48cd-8dc8-e6d45d5b9892"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"1342ec55-602d-4ceb-a0f2-474cd2ae85e0","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Although the examples in this chapter are mainly about options on stocks, there are options on a wide variety of other assets. For example, options are also traded on Treasury securities. These options allow investors to bet on or hedge interest rate risk. There are also options on currencies (we discuss these in more detail in ","marks":[]},{"object":"inline","type":"reference-link","ref":"8316b13d-d853-4363-b8d7-f490b1be761a","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Chapter 23","marks":[]}],"data":{"reference":"98888e90-44e1-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"}},{"object":"text","text":"), gold, platinum, and other commodities such as copper or oil. There are also many options on agricultural products such as wheat, soybeans, livestock, cotton, orange juice, and sugar. These options allow both farmers and large agribusinesses to hedge their risks from fluctuations in production and prices.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"9e00325c-d3fd-4a8d-b878-be4ac55889e4"},{"type":"stage-element-image","config":{"url":{"$ambrosia":"aero:asset:upload","urn":"urn:aero:d658f2b0-44e0-11ed-928f-6f45b86fb3a4","asset":{"urn":"urn:aero:d658f2b0-44e0-11ed-928f-6f45b86fb3a4","asset":{"assetProvider":"ALFRESCO","id":"d658f2b0-44e0-11ed-928f-6f45b86fb3a4","assetMediaType":"image","assetVisibility":"GLOBAL","ownerId":"e88133a0-8dc4-11eb-964e-